<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="65" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="65">
<taxonomicName authority="Baly, 1864" authorityName="Kimoto" authorityYear="1989" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Theopea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Theopea bicolor" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Theopea bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kimoto, 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. bicoloroides" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" rank="species" species="bicoloroides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">T. bicoloroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov., and 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. mouhoti" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" rank="species" species="mouhoti">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">T. mouhoti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Baly are characterized by their reddish brown elytra. 
<taxonomicName authority="Baly, 1864" authorityName="Kimoto" authorityYear="1989" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Theopea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Theopea bicolor" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Theopea bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. bicoloroides" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" rank="species" species="bicoloroides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">T. bicoloroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Habitus of Theopea bicolor, T. bicoloroides sp. nov., and T. mouhoti. A T. bicolor, male, dorsal view B Same, ventral view C T. bicolor, female, dorsal view D T. bicoloroides sp. nov., male, dorsal view E Same, ventral view F T. bicoloroides sp. nov., female, dorsal view G T. mouhoti, male H Same, ventral view I T. mouhoti, female, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.912.47719.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/380656" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">1A-F</figureCitation>
) can be easily separately from 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. mouhoti" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" rank="species" species="mouhoti">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">T. mouhoti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the dark brown or blackish brown head, prothorax, and scutellum, and indistinct ridges on the elytra (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Habitus of Theopea bicolor, T. bicoloroides sp. nov., and T. mouhoti. A T. bicolor, male, dorsal view B Same, ventral view C T. bicolor, female, dorsal view D T. bicoloroides sp. nov., male, dorsal view E Same, ventral view F T. bicoloroides sp. nov., female, dorsal view G T. mouhoti, male H Same, ventral view I T. mouhoti, female, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.912.47719.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/380656" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">1G-I</figureCitation>
). In addition, males of 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. bicolor" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">T. bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. bicoloroides" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" rank="species" species="bicoloroides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">T. bicoloroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. possess median elongate internal aedeagal sclerites that are covered with transverse rows of hair-like setae (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Diagnostic characters of Theopea bicolor. A Antenna, male B Antenna, female C Aedeagus, dorsal view D Aedeagus, lateral view E Aedeagus, ventral view F Abdominal ventrite VIII G Gonocoxae H Spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.912.47719.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/380657" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">2C, D</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Diagnostic characters of Theopea bicoloroides sp. nov. A Antenna, male B Antenna, female C Aedeagus, dorsal view D Aedeagus, lateral view E Aedeagus, ventral view F Abdominal ventrite VIII G Gonocoxae H Spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.912.47719.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/380658" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">3C, D</figureCitation>
). This differs from those of 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. mouhoti" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" rank="species" species="mouhoti">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">T. mouhoti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that lack hair-like setae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Diagnostic characters of Theopea mouhoti. A Antenna, male B Antenna, female C Aedeagus, dorsal view D Same, lateral view E Same, ventral view F Aedeagus, variation, ventral view G Abdominal ventrite VIII H Gonocoxae I Spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.912.47719.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/380659" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">4C, D</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="Baly, 1864" authorityName="Lee &amp; Bezděk" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Theopea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Theopea bicoloroides" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicoloroides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">Theopea bicoloroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. differs from 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. bicolor" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">T. bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the relatively broader antennae in males (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Diagnostic characters of Theopea bicoloroides sp. nov. A Antenna, male B Antenna, female C Aedeagus, dorsal view D Aedeagus, lateral view E Aedeagus, ventral view F Abdominal ventrite VIII G Gonocoxae H Spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.912.47719.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/380658" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">3A</figureCitation>
) (length to width ratios of antennomeres V-X less than 3.0
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
in 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. bicoloroides" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" rank="species" species="bicoloroides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">T. bicoloroides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. but more than 3.0 in 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. bicolor" pageId="0" pageNumber="65" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="65">T. bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
